🚑 RoadRescue – Smart Emergency Response System

🔹 Project Overview

RoadRescue is a real-time emergency response system built to help during road accidents. The idea is simple—when an accident happens, the system quickly detects it and sends alerts to nearby hospitals, ambulances, and emergency contacts.

The main goal is to reduce response time and make sure help reaches the victim as fast as possible.

🔹 🌐 Live Deployement:

👉 https://mypro-two-delta.vercel.app


🔹 🚀 Problem

In many accident cases, the biggest issue is delay:

* People nearby may not act immediately
* Emergency services don’t get accurate location info
* Manual reporting wastes critical time

Even a few minutes can make a huge difference.


🔹 💡 Solution

RoadRescue automates this entire process:

* Detects accidents (or allows quick manual trigger)
* Captures the user’s location
* Sends instant alerts to hospitals and emergency contacts
* Helps initiate faster emergency response


🔹 🧠 Key Features

* Real-time accident detection
* Live location tracking
* Instant emergency alerts
* Ambulance request support
* Nearby hospital identification
* Notification system for contacts
* Simple and clean dashboard


🔹 🛠️ Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Backend:Python (Flask)
Database: MongoDB
APIs: Maps / Notification services

---

🔹 🏗️ How the System Works

```id="fn45cs"
User / Sensor Input  
        ↓  
Accident Detection  
        ↓  
Backend (Flask Server)  
        ↓  
Location + Data Processing  
        ↓  
Alert System  
   ↙            ↘  
Hospitals     Emergency Contacts  



🔹 🧪 Working Flow

1. Accident is detected or triggered
2. System fetches the user’s location
3. Data is sent to the backend
4. Alerts are generated instantly
5. Hospitals and contacts receive notifications
6. Emergency response starts


